{"parse":{"title":"Hilde Lion","pageid":52673474,"revid":773386850,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Hilde Gudilla Lion</b> (1893\u20131970) was a German Jewish academic and teacher of <a href=\"/wiki/Social_worker\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Social worker\">social workers</a> who emigrated to England in 1933, after the <a href=\"/wiki/Nazi_seizure_of_power\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nazi seizure of power\">Nazi seizure of power</a>.  She founded <a href=\"/wiki/Stoatley_Rough_School\" title=\"Stoatley Rough School\">Stoatley Rough School</a> for German refugees in 1934 and was its headmistress until 1960.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5T_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5T-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-LHS_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-LHS-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hilde_Lion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-5T-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5T_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\">\"Dr. Hilde Lion\", <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.geo.brown.edu/BrownNASADataCenter/StoatleyRough/srexhibition/5teachers/5teachers.html\"><i>The Five Principal Teachers at Stoatley Rough</i></a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Dr.+Hilde+Lion&amp;rft.btitle=The+Five+Principal+Teachers+at+Stoatley+Rough&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.geo.brown.edu%2FBrownNASADataCenter%2FStoatleyRough%2Fsrexhibition%2F5teachers%2F5teacher